	<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak direction-ltr">
	<div class="govspeak">
	<h2 id="introduction">Introduction</h2>
	
	<p>Governing bodies, and proprietors of academies and independent schools, are required to hold each of these policies and other documents, as outlined, however:</p>
	
	<ul>
	<li>the drafting of school policies can be delegated to any member of school staff</li>
	<li>there is no requirement for all policies to be reviewed annually</li>
	<li>not all policies need to be signed off by the full governing body</li>
	</ul>
	
	<p>This document also covers how often each policy must be reviewed, and shows the level of approval required where this is prescribed in regulations. Where it doesn’t, we advise you to look at each policy annually. Where there’s a change in the law or circumstances, you will need to revise your policies or documentation accordingly.</p>
	
	<p>There are instances where statutory guidance states that policies and procedures should be in place, although this is not the same as a legal requirement. Each piece of linked guidance makes clear the nature of the requirement.</p>
	
	<h2 id="academies-and-free-schools">Academies and free schools</h2>
	
	<p>They have greater freedoms than maintained schools in relation to school policies and other documents. Where relevant, arrangements applying to these schools are outlined in legislation, or in their <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/academies-financial-handbook">funding agreements</a>, which may vary between individual academies and free schools.</p>
	
	<h2 id="admission-arrangements">Admission arrangements</h2>
	
	<p>These apply to:</p>
	
	<ul>
	<li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
	<li>academies</li>
	<li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
	</ul>
	
	<p>These also apply to voluntary-aided schools and foundation schools directly, and to community and voluntary-controlled schools if the local authority formally delegates the responsibility.</p>
	
	<p>Arrangements for review are determined annually. Any changes must be consulted on, and where no changes are made, consultation is required at least every 7 years.</p>
	
	<p>Full governing body or a committee of the governing body must approve, where the school is an admissions authority.</p>
	
	<div class="call-to-action">
	<p>Statutory guidance to follow when carrying out duties relating to school admissions and school admission appeals:</p>
	
	<ul>
	<li><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/school-admissions-code">School admissions code</a></li>
	<li>
	<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/school-admissions-appeals-code">School admission appeals code</a>.</li>

	</ul>
	
	<p>Guidance about school admissions for children born in the summer:</p>
	
	<ul>
	<li><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/summer-born-children-school-admission">Summer born children school admissions</a></li>

	</ul>
	</div>
	
	<h2 id="administration-and-staff">Administration and staff</h2>
	
	<h3 id="capability-of-staff-and-teacher-appraisals">Capability of staff and teacher appraisals</h3>
	
	<p>Applies to:</p>
	
	<ul>
	<li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
	<li>pupil referral units (<abbr title="pupil referral unit">PRU</abbr>)</li>
	</ul>
	
	<p>The governing body is free to determine frequency of review and to delegate approval to a committee of the governing body or an individual governor.</p>
	
	<div class="call-to-action">
	<p>Guidance for schools on appraisal and dismissal policies: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/teacher-appraisal-and-capability-model-policy">Teacher appraisal and capability model policy</a></p>

	</div>
	
	<h3 id="charging-and-remissions">Charging and remissions</h3>
	
	<p>Applies to:</p>
	
	<ul>
	<li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
	<li>academies</li>
	<li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
	</ul>
	
	<p>The governing body is free to determine frequency of review and delegate approval to a committee of the governing body, an individual governor or the headteacher.</p>
	
	<p>This applies directly to academies and free schools via their funding agreements.</p>
	
	<div class="call-to-action">
	<p>Guidance on how to set out policies on charging for school activities and visits: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/charging-for-school-activities">Charging for school activities</a></p>

	</div>
	
	<h3 id="data-protection">Data protection</h3>
	
	<p>Applies to:</p>
	
	<ul>
	<li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
	<li>academies</li>
	<li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
	<li>independent schools, not state-funded</li>
	<li>sixth-form colleges</li>
	<li>further education colleges with 16 to 19 provision</li>
	<li>pupil referral units (<abbr title="pupil referral unit">PRU</abbr>)</li>
	<li>non-maintained special schools</li>
	</ul>
	
	<p>Under the Data Protection (Charges and Information) Regulations 2018, schools must register with the <a rel="external" href="http://ico.org.uk/for_organisations/data_protection/registration">information commissioner’s office</a>.</p>
	
	<p>Review at least every 2 years, registration is annual.</p>
	
	<div class="call-to-action">
	<p>Suggested privacy notices to issue to staff, parents and pupils about the collection of data: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/data-protection-and-privacy-privacy-notices">Data protection and privacy notices</a></p>

	</div>
	
	<h3 id="freedom-of-information">Freedom of Information</h3>
	
	<p>Applies to:</p>
	
	<ul>
	<li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
	<li>academies</li>
	<li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
	<li>pupil referral units (<abbr title="pupil referral unit">PRU</abbr>)</li>
	</ul>
	
	<p>This applies to local authorities on behalf of PRUs. The governing body is free to determine frequency of review and to determine how to implement approval.</p>
	
	<p>Further information is on the <a rel="external" href="http://www.ico.org.uk/for_organisations/freedom_of_information">information commissioner’s office website</a>.</p>
	
	<h3 id="protection-of-biometric-information-of-children-in-schools-and-colleges">Protection of biometric information of children in schools and colleges</h3>
	
	<p>This applies to:</p>
	
	<ul>
	<li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
	<li>academies</li>
	<li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
	<li>independent schools, not state-funded</li>
	<li>sixth-form colleges</li>
	<li>pupil referral units (<abbr title="pupil referral unit">PRU</abbr>)</li>
	<li>non-maintained special schools</li>
	</ul>
	
	<p>Guidance on the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/protection-of-biometric-information-of-children-in-schools">protection of biometric information of children in schools and colleges</a>.</p>
	
	<h3 id="register-of-pupils-admission-to-school-and-attendance">Register of pupils’ admission to school and attendance</h3>
	
	<p>Applies to:</p>
	
	<ul>
	<li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
	<li>academies</li>
	<li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
	<li>independent schools, not state-funded</li>
	<li>pupil referral units (<abbr title="pupil referral unit">PRU</abbr>)</li>
	<li>non-maintained special schools</li>
	</ul>
	
	<p>The register of admission must be a live document. The governing body is free to delegate approval to a committee of the governing body, an individual governor or the headteacher or the proprietor.</p>
	
	<p>The register itself can be kept by appropriate school staff.</p>
	
	<p>The attendance register must be a live document. The governing body of a school can delegate the keeping of the register to the headteacher. The register can be kept and updated daily by appropriate school staff.</p>
	
	<div class="call-to-action">
	<p>Guidance on using pupil registers and attendance codes, as well as setting school hours and term dates: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/school-attendance">School attendance</a></p>

	</div>
	
	<h3 id="school-complaints">School complaints</h3>
	
	<p>Applies to:</p>
	
	<ul>
	<li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
	<li>academies</li>
	<li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
	<li>independent schools, not state-funded</li>
	<li>pupil referral units (<abbr title="pupil referral unit">PRU</abbr>)</li>
	<li>non-maintained special schools</li>
	</ul>
	
	<p>The governing body or the proprietor are free to determine frequency of review and delegate approval to a committee of the governing body, an individual governor or the headteacher.</p>
	
	<div class="call-to-action">
	<p>Guidance for schools on setting up and reviewing complaints procedures: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/school-complaints-procedures">School complaints procedures</a></p>
	</div>
	
	<h3 id="school-information-published-on-a-website">School information published on a website</h3>
	
	<p>Applies to:</p>
	
	<ul>
	<li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
	<li>academies</li>
	<li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
	</ul>
	
	<p>This is a live document that must be updated as soon as possible after a change and at least annually. The governing body is free to delegate approval to a committee of the governing body, an individual governor or the headteacher.</p>
	
	<div class="call-to-action">
	<p>Details of the information to include on websites:</p>
	
	<ul>
	<li>
	<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/what-maintained-schools-must-publish-online">What maintained schools must publish online</a></p>

	</li>
	<li>
	<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/what-academies-free-schools-and-colleges-should-publish-online">What academies, free schools and colleges should publish online</a></p>
	</li>
	</ul>
	</div>
	
	<h3 id="school-staff-driving-minibuses-driving-licences">School staff driving minibuses: driving licences</h3>
	
	<p>Applies to:</p>
	
	<ul>
	<li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
	<li>academies</li>
	<li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
	<li>independent schools, not state-funded</li>
	<li>sixth-form colleges</li>
	<li>pupil referral units (<abbr title="pupil referral unit">PRU</abbr>)</li>
	<li>non-maintained special schools</li>
	</ul>
	
	<div class="call-to-action">
	<p>Advice on when a school employee with a car driving licence may drive a minibus and when a section 19 permit might be required: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/driving-school-minibuses-advice-for-schools-and-local-authorities">School staff driving minibuses: driving licences</a></p>

	</div>
	
	<h3 id="staff-discipline-conduct-and-grievance-procedures-for-addressing">Staff discipline, conduct and grievance (procedures for addressing)</h3>
	
	<p>Applies to:</p>
	
	<ul>
	<li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
	<li>academies</li>
	<li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
	<li>independent schools, not state-funded</li>
	<li>sixth-form colleges</li>
	<li>pupil referral units (<abbr title="pupil referral unit">PRU</abbr>)</li>
	<li>non-maintained special schools</li>
	</ul>
	
	<p>For maintained schools, the governing body is free to determine frequency of review. All other establishments may want to include this policy but should refer to general employment law.</p>
	
	<p>For maintained schools the governing body must approve.</p>
	
	<p>For academies the governing body is free to delegate approval to a committee of the governing body, an individual governor or the headteacher.</p>
	
	<div class="call-to-action">
	<p>Guidance for managing staff and employment issues: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/staffing-and-employment-advice-for-schools">Staffing and employment advice for schools</a></p>

	</div>
	
	<h3 id="statement-of-procedures-for-dealing-with-allegations-of-abuse-against-staff">Statement of procedures for dealing with allegations of abuse against staff</h3>
	
	<p>Applies to:</p>
	
	<ul>
	<li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
	<li>academies</li>
	<li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
	<li>independent schools, not state-funded</li>
	<li>sixth-form colleges</li>
	<li>further education colleges with 16 to 19 provision</li>
	<li>pupil referral units (<abbr title="pupil referral unit">PRU</abbr>)</li>
	<li>non-maintained special schools</li>
	</ul>
	
	<p>The governing body is free to determine frequency of review and approval.</p>
	
	<div class="call-to-action">
	<p>Statutory guidance on safeguarding children and safer recruitment: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/disqualification-under-the-childcare-act-2006">Disqualification under the childcare act 2006</a> and <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/keeping-children-safe-in-education">Keeping children safe in education</a></p>

	</div>
	
	<h3 id="single-central-record-of-recruitment-and-vetting-checks">Single central record of recruitment and vetting checks</h3>
	
	<p>Applies to:</p>
	
	<ul>
	<li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
	<li>academies</li>
	<li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
	<li>independent schools, not state-funded</li>
	<li>sixth-form colleges</li>
	<li>pupil referral units (<abbr title="pupil referral unit">PRU</abbr>)</li>
	<li>non-maintained special schools</li>
	</ul>
	
	<p>This is a live document covering staff currently employed. The governing body is free to delegate approval to a committee of the governing body, an individual governor or the headteacher.</p>
	
	<div class="call-to-action">
	<p>Statutory guidance on employing staff who have been disqualified from providing childcare: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/keeping-children-safe-in-education">Keeping children safe in education</a> and <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/disqualification-under-the-childcare-act-2006">Disqualification under the childcare act 2006</a></p>

	
	<p>This applies to all schools, colleges and further education institutions where early years education is delivered. Linked to safeguarding policies.</p>
	</div>
	
	<h3 id="teachers-pay">Teachers’ pay</h3>
	
	<p>Applies to:</p>
	
	<ul>
	<li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
	</ul>
	
	<p>This must be reviewed annually and the governing body will need to approve.</p>
	
	<div class="call-to-action">
	<p>Statutory guidance on pay and conditions for teachers: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/school-teachers-pay-and-conditions">Teachers’ pay and conditions</a></p>

	</div>
	
	<h2 id="pupil-wellbeing-and-behaviour">Pupil wellbeing and behaviour</h2>
	
	<h3 id="accessibility-plan">Accessibility plan</h3>
	
	<p>Applies to:</p>
	
	<ul>
	<li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
	<li>academies</li>
	<li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
	<li>independent schools, not state-funded</li>
	<li>sixth-form colleges</li>
	<li>pupil referral units (<abbr title="pupil referral unit">PRU</abbr>)</li>
	<li>non-maintained special schools</li>
	</ul>
	
	<p>Review every 3 years.</p>
	
	<p>The governing body is free to delegate approval to a committee of the governing body, an individual governor or the headteacher.</p>
	
	<p>Guidance on accessibility plans is included in our <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/equality-act-2010-advice-for-schools">Equality act 2010 advice for schools</a> to help schools fulfil their duties under the act.</p>
	
	<h3 id="behaviour-in-schools">Behaviour in schools</h3>
	
	<p>Applies to:</p>
	
	<ul>
	<li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
	<li>academies</li>
	<li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
	<li>independent schools, not state-funded</li>
	<li>pupil referral units (<abbr title="pupil referral unit">PRU</abbr>)</li>
	<li>non-maintained special schools</li>
	</ul>
	
	<p>the headteacher is free to determine frequency of review and approval.</p>
	
	<h3 id="behaviour-principles-written-statement">Behaviour principles written statement</h3>
	
	<p>Applies to:</p>
	
	<ul>
	<li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
	<li>pupil referral units (<abbr title="pupil referral unit">PRU</abbr>)</li>
	<li>non-maintained special schools</li>
	</ul>
	
	<p>The governing body is free to determine frequency of review. The full governing body or a committee of the governing body to approve.</p>
	
	<div class="call-to-action">
	<p>Statutory guidance on creating a behaviour policy: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/behaviour-and-discipline-in-schools-guidance-for-governing-bodies">Behaviour and discipline in schools: guide for governing bodies</a></p>
	</div>
	
	<h3 id="child-protection-policy-and-procedures">Child protection policy and procedures</h3>
	
	<p>Applies to:</p>
	
	<ul>
	<li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
	<li>academies</li>
	<li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
	<li>independent schools, not state-funded</li>
	<li>sixth-form colleges</li>
	<li>pupil referral units (<abbr title="pupil referral unit">PRU</abbr>)</li>
	<li>non-maintained special schools</li>
	</ul>
	
	<p>Review annually. The governing body or proprietor to approve.</p>
	
	<div class="call-to-action">
	<p>Statutory guidance on safeguarding children and safer recruitment: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/keeping-children-safe-in-education">Keeping children safe in education</a></p>

	</div>
	
	<h3 id="early-years-foundation-stage-eyfs">Early Years Foundation Stage (<abbr title="early years foundation stage">EYFS</abbr>)</h3>
	
	<p>Applies to:</p>
	
	<ul>
	<li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
	<li>academies</li>
	<li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
	<li>independent schools, not state-funded</li>
	<li>pupil referral units (<abbr title="pupil referral unit">PRU</abbr>)</li>
	<li>non-maintained special schools</li>
	</ul>
	
	<p>Those delivering the <abbr title="early years foundation stage">EYFS</abbr> are required to have policies and procedures on a range of issues covering safeguarding and welfare. These are set out in detail in the ‘Statutory framework for the early years foundation stage’.</p>
	
	<p>Schools are not required to have separate policies to cover <abbr title="early years foundation stage">EYFS</abbr> requirements where they are already met through an existing policy. An <abbr title="early years foundation stage">EYFS</abbr> profile assessment is required for each child during the academic year they reach the age of 5 (for most children this is the reception year in primary school) and nursery settings catering for children under 3 must complete a summary check when a child is aged 2.</p>
	
	<p>Review frequency varies, details are in the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/early-learning-and-childcare-guidance-for-early-years-providers">Statutory framework for the Early Years Foundation Stage</a>.</p>
	
	<p>Governing body free to determine approval.</p>
	
	<h3 id="first-aid-in-schools">First aid in schools</h3>
	
	<p>Applies to:</p>
	
	<ul>
	<li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
	<li>academies</li>
	<li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
	<li>independent schools, not state-funded</li>
	<li>sixth-form colleges</li>
	<li>pupil referral units (<abbr title="pupil referral unit">PRU</abbr>)</li>
	<li>non-maintained special schools</li>
	</ul>
	
	<div class="call-to-action">
	<p>Guidance on first aid provision: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/first-aid-in-schools">First aid in schools</a></p>
	</div>
	
	<h3 id="school-exclusion">School exclusion</h3>
	
	<p>Applies to:</p>
	
	<ul>
	<li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
	<li>academies and free schools</li>
	<li>pupil referral units (<abbr title="pupil referral unit">PRU</abbr>)</li>
	</ul>
	
	<div class="call-to-action">
	<p>Statutory guidance on the exclusion of pupils: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/school-exclusion">School exclusion</a></p>
	</div>
	
	<h3 id="sex-education">Sex education</h3>
	
	<p>Applies to:</p>
	
	<ul>
	<li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
	<li>academies</li>
	<li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
	<li>pupil referral units (<abbr title="pupil referral unit">PRU</abbr>)</li>
	</ul>
	
	<p>Does not apply to maintained nursery schools.</p>
	
	<p>Governing body free to determine frequency of review. Governing body free to delegate approval to a committee of the governing body, an individual governor or the headteacher.</p>
	
	<div class="call-to-action">
	<p>Statutory guidance on sex and relationship education: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/sex-and-relationship-education">Sex and relationship education</a></p>
	</div>
	
	<h3 id="special-educational-needs-and-disability">Special educational needs and disability</h3>
	
	<p>Applies to:</p>
	
	<ul>
	<li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
	<li>academies</li>
	<li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
	</ul>
	
	<p>The SEN Information Report should be updated annually and any changes to the information occurring during the year should be updated as soon as possible. Full governing body or proprietor to approve.</p>
	
	<div class="call-to-action">
	<p>Statutory guidance on the special educational needs and disability (SEND) system for children and young people: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/send-code-of-practice-0-to-25">The 0 to 25 special educational needs and disability code of practice</a>.</p>
	</div>
	
	<h3 id="supporting-pupils-with-medical-conditions">Supporting pupils with medical conditions</h3>
	
	<p>Applies to:</p>
	
	<ul>
	<li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
	<li>academies</li>
	<li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
	<li>pupil referral units (<abbr title="pupil referral unit">PRU</abbr>)</li>
	</ul>
	
	<p>Governing bodies, proprietors and management committees free to determine frequency of review. Governing bodies to approve for maintained schools, proprietors of academies, and management committees of pupil referral units.</p>
	
	<div class="call-to-action">
	<p>Statutory guidance about the support that pupils with medical conditions should receive: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/supporting-pupils-at-school-with-medical-conditions--3">Supporting pupils at school with medical conditions</a></p>

	</div>
	
	<h2 id="facilities">Facilities</h2>
	
	<h3 id="health-and-safety">Health and safety</h3>
	
	<p>Applies to:</p>
	
	<ul>
	<li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
	<li>academies</li>
	<li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
	<li>independent schools, not state-funded</li>
	<li>pupil referral units (<abbr title="pupil referral unit">PRU</abbr>)</li>
	</ul>
	
	<p>Also applies to local authorities on behalf of community and voluntary-controlled schools and PRUs.</p>
	
	<p>Governing body, proprietor or local authority free to determine frequency of review. Employer free to determine how to implement and approve.</p>
	
	<div class="call-to-action">
	<p>Advice on health and safety covering activities: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/health-and-safety-advice-for-schools">Health and safety advice for schools</a></p>

	</div>
	
	<h3 id="premises-management-documents">Premises management documents</h3>
	
	<p>Applies to:</p>
	
	<ul>
	<li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
	<li>academies</li>
	<li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
	<li>independent schools, not state-funded</li>
	<li>sixth-form colleges</li>
	<li>pupil referral units (<abbr title="pupil referral unit">PRU</abbr>)</li>
	<li>non-maintained special schools</li>
	</ul>
	
	<p>There are many aspects of school premises that require safe management and maintenance such as asbestos, fire safety and statutory testing. Those with duties for maintaining school buildings should make sure that the policies, procedures and the condition of the estate are compliant with appropriate legislation, including health and safety.</p>
	
	<p>Independent schools, academies and free schools have sole responsibility.</p>
	
	<p>For maintained schools, both local authorities and schools have responsibilities for the repair and maintenance of premises.</p>
	
	<p>Governing body free to delegate approval to a committee of the governing body, an individual governor or the headteacher.</p>
	
	<div class="call-to-action">
	<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/good-estate-management-for-schools/the-fundamentals-of-good-estate-management">Good estate management for schools advice</a> on the policies, processes and documents that schools, academies and multi-academy trusts should consider when managing their estates.</p>
	</div>
	
	<p>Additional non-statutory advice on <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/asbestos-management-in-schools">asbestos management in schools</a>.</p>

	
	<p>Guidance on completing a <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/fire-safety-risk-assessment-educational-premises">fire safety risk assessment for educational premises</a>.</p>
	
	<p>Independent schools, academies and free schools have sole responsibility.</p>
	
	<p>For maintained schools, both local authorities and schools have responsibilities for the repair and maintenance of premises.</p>
	
	<p>Governing body free to delegate approval to a committee of the governing body, an individual governor or the headteacher.</p>
	
	<div class="call-to-action">
	<p>Guidance to help schools and local authorities understand their obligations in relation to the School Premises Regulations 2012: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/standards-for-school-premises">Standards for school premises</a></p>

	</div>
	
	<h2 id="governors-and-school-leaders">Governors and school leaders</h2>
	
	<h3 id="equality-information-and-objectives-public-sector-equality-duty-statement-for-publication">Equality information and objectives (public sector equality duty) statement for publication</h3>
	
	<p>Applies to:</p>
	
	<ul>
	<li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
	<li>academies</li>
	<li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
	<li>pupil referral units (<abbr title="pupil referral unit">PRU</abbr>)</li>
	</ul>
	
	<p>Applies to local authorities on behalf of PRUs.</p>
	
	<p>Review every 4 years and publish information annually. Governing body free to delegate approval to a committee of the governing body, an individual governor or the headteacher.</p>
	
	<p>Under specific duties, governing bodies, local authorities and proprietors are required to draw up and publish equality objectives every 4 years and annually publish information demonstrating how they are meeting the aims of the general public sector equality duty.</p>
	
	<h3 id="governors-allowances-schemes-for-paying">Governors’ allowances (schemes for paying)</h3>
	
	<p>Applies to:</p>
	
	<ul>
	<li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
	</ul>
	
	<p>Governing body free to determine frequency of review. Governing body free to delegate approval to a committee of the governing body, an individual governor or the headteacher.</p>
	
	<h3 id="instrument-of-government">Instrument of government</h3>
	
	<p>Applies to:</p>
	
	<ul>
	<li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
	</ul>
	
	<p>Governing body free to determine frequency of review.
	Full governing body to approve.</p>
	
	<div class="call-to-action">
	<p>Guidance on the roles and duties of governing boards, and advice on the skills, knowledge and behaviours they need to be effective: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/governance-handbook">Governance handbook</a></p>
	</div>
	
	<h3 id="minutes-of-and-papers-considered-at-meetings-of-the-governing-body-and-its-committees">Minutes of, and papers considered at, meetings of the governing body and its committees</h3>
	
	<p>Applies to:</p>
	
	<ul>
	<li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
	<li>academies</li>
	<li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
	<li>pupil referral units (<abbr title="pupil referral unit">PRU</abbr>)</li>
	</ul>
	
	<p>Full governing body or a committee of the governing body to approve as appropriate.</p>
	
	<h3 id="register-of-business-interests-of-headteachers-and-governors">Register of business interests of headteachers and governors</h3>
	
	<p>Applies to:</p>
	
	<ul>
	<li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
	<li>academies</li>
	</ul>
	
	<p>Governing body free to determine frequency of review and approval subject to the local authority scheme.</p>
	
	<div class="call-to-action">
	<p>Statutory guidance for local authorities on producing and amending school financing schemes: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/schemes-for-financing-schools">Schemes for financing schools</a></p>

	
	<p>Statutory guidance setting out the arrangements for the constitution of governing bodies of all local authority maintained schools: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/constitution-of-governing-bodies-of-maintained-schools">Constitution of governing bodies of maintained schools</a></p>

	</div>
	
	</div>
	</div>
	</div>
	
