scribed in regulations. Where it doesn’t, we advise you to look at each policy annually. Where there’s a change in the law or circumstances, you will need to revise your policies or documentation accordingly.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThere are instances where statutory guidance states that policies and procedures should be in place, although this is not the same as a legal requirement. Each piece of linked guidance makes clear the nature of the requirement.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"academies-and-free-schools\"\u003eAcademies and free schools\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThey have greater freedoms than maintained schools in relation to school policies and other documents. Where relevant, arrangements applying to these schools are outlined in legislation, or in their \u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/academies-financial-handbook\"\u003efunding agreements\u003c/a\u003e, which may vary between individual academies and free schools.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"admission-arrangements\"\u003eAdmission arrangements\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThese apply to:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n \u003cli\u003emaintained schools, including maintained special schools\u003c/li\u003e\n \u003cli\u003eacademies\u003c/li\u003e\n \u003cli\u003efree schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThese also apply to voluntary-aided schools and foundation schools directly, and to community and voluntary-controlled schools if the local authority formally delegates the responsibility.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eArrangements for review are determined annually. Any changes must be consulted on, and where no changes are made, consultation is required at least every 7 years.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eFull governing body or a committee of the governing body must approve, where the school is an admissions authority.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv class=\"call-to-action\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eStatutory guidance to follow when carrying out duties relating to school admissions and school admission appeals:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/school-admissions-code\"\u003eSchool admissions code\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n \u003cli\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/school-admissions-appeals-code\"\u003eSchool admission appeals code\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eGuidance about school admissions for children born in the summer:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/summer-born-children-school-admission\"\u003eSummer born children school admissions\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"administration-and-staff\"\u003eAdministration and staff\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003ch3 id=\"capability-of-staff-and-teacher-appraisals\"\u003eCapability of staff and teacher appraisals\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eApplies to:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n \u003cli\u003emaintained schools, including maintained special schools\u003c/li\u003e\n \u003cli\u003epupil referral units (\u003cabbr title=\"pupil referral unit\"\u003ePRU\u003c/abbr\u003e)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe governing body is free to determine frequency of review and to delegate approval to a committee of the governing body or an individual governor.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv class=\"call-to-action\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eGuidance for schools on appraisal and dismissal policies: \u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/teacher-appraisal-and-capability-model-policy\"\u003eTeacher appraisal and capability model policy\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3 id=\"charging-and-remissions\"\u003eCharging and remissions\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eApplies to:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n \u003cli\u003emaintained schools, including maintained special schools\u003c/li\u003e\n \u003cli\u003eacademies\u003c/li\u003e\n \u003cli\u003efree schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe governing body is free to determine frequency of review and delegate approval to a committee of the governing body, an individual governor or the headteacher.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis applies directly to academies and free schools via their funding agreements.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv class=\"call-to-action\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eGuidance on how to set out policies on charging for school activities and visits: \u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/charging-for-school-activities\"\u003eCharging for school activities\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3 id=\"data-protection\"\u003eData protection\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eApplies to:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n \u003cli\u003emaintained schools, including maintained special schools\u003c/li\u003e\n \u003cli\u003eacademies\u003c/li\u003e\n \u003cli\u003efree schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools\u003c/li\u003e\n \u003cli\u003eindependent schools, not state-funded\u003c/li\u003e\n \u003cli\u003esixth-form colleges\u003c/li\u003e\n \u003cli\u003efurther education colleges with 16 to 19 provision\u003c/li\u003e\n \u003cli\u003epupil referral units (\u003cabbr title=\"pupil referral unit\"\u003ePRU\u003c/abbr\u003e)\u003c/li\u003e\n \u003cli\u003enon-maintained special schools\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eUnder the Data Protection (Charges and Information) Regulations 2018, schools must register with the \u003ca rel=\"external\" href=\"http://ico.org.uk/for_organisations/data_protection/registration\"\u003einformation commissioner’s office\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eReview at least every 2 years, registration is annual.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv class=\"call-to-action\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSuggested privacy notices to issue to staff, parents and pupils about the collection of data: \u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/data-protection-and-privacy-privacy-notices\"\u003eData protection and privacy notices\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3 id=\"freedom-of-information\"\u003eFreedom of Information\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eApplies to:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n \u003cli\u003emaintained schools, including maintained special schools\u003c/li\u003e\n \u003cli\u003eacademies\u003c/li\u003e\n \u003cli\u003efree schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools\u003c/li\u003e\n \u003cli\u003epupil referral units (\u003cabbr title=\"pupil referral unit\"\u003ePRU\u003c/abbr\u003e)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis applies to local authorities on behalf of PRUs. The governing body is free to determine frequency of review and to determine how to implement approval.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eFurther information is on the \u003ca rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.ico.org.uk/for_organisations/freedom_of_information\"\u003einformation commissioner’s office website\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3 id=\"protection-of-biometric-information-of-children-in-schools-and-colleges\"\u003eProtection of biometric information of children in schools and colleges\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis applies to:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n \u003cli\u003emaintained schools, including maintained special schools\u003c/li\u003e\n \u003cli\u003eacademies\u003c/li\u003e\n \u003cli\u003efree schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools\u003c/li\u003e\n \u003cli\u003eindependent schools, not state-funded\u003c/li\u003e\n \u003cli\u003esixth-form colleges\u003c/li\u003e\n \u003cli\u003epupil referral units (\u003cabbr title=\"pupil referral unit\"\u003ePRU\u003c/abbr\u003e)\u003c/li\u003e\n \u003cli\u003enon-maintained special schools\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eGuidance on the \u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/protection-of-biometric-information-of-children-in-schools\"\u003eprotection of biometric information of children in schools and colleges\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3 id=\"register-of-pupils-admission-to-school-and-attendance\"\u003eRegister of pupils’ admission to school and attendance\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eApplies to:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n \u003cli\u003emaintained schools, including maintained special schools\u003c/li\u003e\n \u003cli\u003eacademies\u003c/li\u003e\n \u003cli\u003efree schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools\u003c/li\u003e\n \u003cli\u003eindependent schools, not state-funded\u003c/li\u003e\n \u003cli\u003epupil referral units (\u003cabbr title=\"pupil referral unit\"\u003ePRU\u003c/abbr\u003e)\u003c/li\u003e\n \u003cli\u003enon-maintained special schools\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe register of admission must be a live document. The governing body is free to delegate approval to a committee of the governing body, an individual governor or the headteacher or the proprietor.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe register itself can be kept by appropriate school staff.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe attendance register must be a live document. The governing body of a school can delegate the keeping of the register to the headteacher. The register can be kept and updated daily by appropriate school staff.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv class=\"call-to-action\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eGuidance on using pupil registers and attendance codes, as well as setting school hours and term dates: \u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/school-attendance\"\u003eSchool attendance\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch3 id=\"school-complaints\"\u003eSchool complaints\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eApplies to:\u003c/p\